    "topic":  "01. Staff Welfare",
    "title":  "Holiday",
    "category":  "Policy",
    "description":  "Holidays and sickness \nThe normal sickness notification procedures will apply to an employee when they are on leave and wish to reallocate the period of leave as sickness with the result that reconvened leave may be taken at another time in the leave year. Where the required notification is made, the Company may permit those days to be classed as sick days and equivalent time off taken as paid leave later in the leave year provide the leave falls within the statutory minimum entitlement. The days on which the leave is to be taken must be agreed with the Company. Employees who are on an overseas holiday when they fall sick should contact the Company as soon as reasonably practicable.",
